Who would have guessed that a wall would get a rating of 4 1/2 stars?  
It's an awesome wall for sure, stopping even the most broken of of Turn 2-3 attackers (where's your [Abyssal Persecutor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Abyssal Persecutor) now?  

@Scumbling: Buying time is a critical aspect of the game. Nobody said that I was playing walls instead of game-winning spells and abilities. Reliably and repeatedly buying time isn't good on it's own, and filling a deck with only that results in a lot of slow defeats. But if you buy time efficiently and early enough, it gives you more time to ramp mana and drop those finishers, because ramping and playing creatures takes up time, and this has unprecedented delaying power at a relatively manageable cost. On top of all that, a lot of decks burn themselves out quickly, if they can't get through those first few turns. Defenders repeatedly thwart their attempts at getting through, which means that after they've emptied their hand, all they can do is wait for you to draw your f... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)

